<p>This system provides an online portal analogous to a public library where registered patrons can &quot;borrow&quot; books. The main difference being, that the books in the library catalog are all in electronic formats that incorporate Digital Rights Management (DRM). This lets the system “lend” an allowed number of copies to registered users. In addition, when a book has the proper rights, the E-Library can sell patrons a license for a personal copy of the electronic book that they can retain permanently.</p>
